## 📊 Portfolio vs Benchmark Analysis (Python)

### 🎯 Purpose
It is essential to compare a portfolio against a benchmark in order to evaluate
whether the current asset allocation is coherent with the investor’s risk profile.

This project focuses on comparing a custom multi-asset portfolio with a
100% MSCI World benchmark over a selected time horizon.

The objective is not to perform a long-term backtest, but to evaluate
short-term performance and risk-adjusted returns.

---

### 🔍 Approach
- Definition of a multi-asset portfolio using common European ETFs
- Flexible selection of start and end dates
- Comparison against MSCI World as a global equity benchmark
- Focus on risk-adjusted performance rather than absolute returns

---

###  Portfolio Composition
The portfolio is built using representative asset trackers:
- S&P 500 (US equities)
- MSCI Europe
- Asian equities
- European government bonds
- Gold

Asset weights, tickers and descriptions can be freely modified to adapt
the analysis to different investor profiles.

---

### 📊 Metrics
- Annualized return
- Volatility
- Sharpe ratio
- Visual comparison with benchmark performance

---

### ⚠️ Disclaimer
This project is for educational and analytical purposes only and does not
constitute investment advice.
